President Cyril Ramaphosa has appointed his Deputy David Mabuza as his Special Envoy to the Russian Federation on Tuesday where he will meet with President Vladimir Putin. Mabuza will on behalf of President Ramaphosa extend a message of congratulations to Putin following his re-election as President and is scheduled to meet with him tomorrow. Putin was inaugurated for his fourth term as President of the Russian Federation last week. He has since become the longest-serving Russian president since former leader Joseph Stalin. In a statement, the presidency says that Ramaphosa is looking forward strengthening the already existing political and economic and trade ties that exist between the country and Russia. “These relations are underpinned by the common values the two countries share with regard to respect for the rule of law in international relations, multilateralism, the central role of the United Nations in global governance…” reads a statement by the Presidency. Putin is expected to be in South Africa in July alongside other Heads of State of the Brazil Russia India China South Africa (BRICS) bloc of nations at the forthcoming BRICS Summit. -Afro Reporter